  "texts": [
    "Hence, f is an isomorphism of twisted principal N-bundles.",
    "It therefore preserves vertical invariant fields, thus giving rise to a vector bundle isomorphism f ad: adM 1 → adM 2 which is of course a fibrewise isometry with respect to the bundle metrics h 1, h 2.",
    "From f * (H 1) = H 2 we deduce that f * ad ∇ ad,2 = ∇ ad,1.",
    "Conversely, suppose that we are given f ad and f satisfying (i) and (ii).",
    "By replacing M 2 with f * M 2, we may assume that f ad covers the identity."
